Problem: Still low LTV. Annual membership at $99 + average 12 scans = $159 total. Better, but still worse than $12/month recurring.

My Recommendation: Option A (Freemium → Pro Subscription)
Here's why:

Metric	Pay-Per-Use ($12)	Pro Subscription ($12/mo)
Customer LTV	$12–50 (one-time)	$144–180/year
Retention	0% (one-time)	70–85% (sticky)
Expansion revenue	None	Upsell to Agency tier
Predictable revenue	No	Yes (MRR)
SaaS valuation multiple	2–3x ARR	8–12x ARR
Unit economics	Negative	Positive
The shift: Move from transactional to recurring, which is the entire basis of SaaS profitability.

